product.description: Here is my 2010 Honda CBR 125-R For Sale as I am moving onto a bigger bike. The good: - This model is the sportier option to a 125, is has a very modest 13 bhp output and is liquid cooled as well as fuel injected meaning you will get a little more speed in quicker time as well as being able to ride for long periods of time without risk of the engine overheating. -The CBR has a 10 litre fuel tank and will easily do 72mpg/155 miles on a full tank. The fact this bikes fuel tank is fairly small means its cheap as chips to fill and will last well over a week of city commuting as well a little fun on the country roads. -As the bike is classed as the supersport model of its era it comes with a set of very nice angular panels but still shows off a bit of engine. I have kept these panels very tidy and clean so as a result the bike looks great and comes up nice after a good scrub! -Although the bike is only a 125 the speed you can achieve is very good, I used to commute 70 miles up to Wales and never had any issues with keeping up with other vehicles and even managed some cheeky overtakes on the way. I am confident in saying the bike will sit comfortably at 70 mph all day long and with a steep hill and wind on your back will push 80 mph (rider discretion advised!!). - I have kept my CBR in very good condition for the year that I have had it, regular servicing was always a priority for me as I was commuting such a long distance. I have a full set of service history papers but please note this is only from the last year. I have had front and rear tyres put (Continental Conti GO's) on and these have plenty of tread left. As a result of continued servicing the bike flew through its MOT in February and is valid for another year. -The bike is fairly comfortable and is definitely suitable for longer commutes on dual carriageways and motorways as well short city rides. -The Honda is a very forgiving bike and can cope with new riders who are a little less confident with gears (don't worry, we all have to start somewhere!) and is easy to control and move around at lower speeds. At higher speeds the Honda has absolutely no trouble holding it's own and can be thrown around with very little effort which is ideal for riders who are just starting out. Another thing this bike is equipped with is a very sturdy powerful set of disk brakes (front and rear) which are an absolute god send when you haven't ridden a geared bike before and will never fail to stop you very quickly and comfortably in emergency situations. The bad: -Unfortunately due a very clumsy previous owner the bike was presumably dropped and as a result the exhaust has a fairly large scratch (pictured above). Another issue that has resulted from the bike being dropped is a slightly bent swing arm but I must stress that this in no way effects the bike and if anything just looks a little untidy (also very hard to photograph). The bike has a few very minor and hardly noticeable scratches that are from everyday wear and tear. -As the bike is getting on for 6 years old there is a small patch of rust near the handlebars but I have kept a close eye on this and have used WD-40 to prevent any further spread or deterioration. -As seen pictured above I do have the right hand side indicator wrapped in duct tape as the rubber parts are slightly worn so don't properly connect to form a seal, this is probably very easily fixed by someone who knows how fix a bike or as I've done...with duct tape. The Ugly: - As stated above this bike has been very well looked after and regularly serviced so there isn't really much 'ugly' on my Honda. I have made every effort to keep the panels looking nice and have also made sure to keep her clean when the weather permits me to. Conclusion: - This bike has been very well looked after and very loved in my possession, it's been an absolute joy to ride and will start up every time on the button (or your money back...just kidding). If you are looking to move onto something with a little more power after a moped then this is the bike for you! The Honda CBR 125-R provides a great time in the hills and a nice comfy ride in the city environments and I like to think mine is a great example of one that's been well looked after. If you'd like to come have a look around her then please give me a call or you can email me. I regret to say that test rides are only available once you've paid. Please NO TIME WASTERS! If you would like to see any more pictures or need any more info then give me a call or email me and I will happily send some over!

product.productName: Aprilia RSV Mille R, 2003 gen 1, 1000 R
product.description: Selling my 2003 single seat Aprilia RSV Mille R with 21151 miles on the clock. MOT until 10th April 2017. £3500 ovno. I'll get the bad bit out of the way first. There are some scratches on the right hand fairings where I had a 15mph lowside slide due to diesel on a roundabout. The damage is purely cosmetic and has not affected the structure or ride of the bike in any way. On with the good bits. Apart from the above she is a very clean, honest bike with some age related marks. She is the last of the gen 1 Milles with the black frame and swingarm (best looking imo), Ohlins front and rear suspension (no weeps, seeps or leaks) , Ohlins steering damper, lightweight forged aluminium Oz wheels, Brembo radial callipers and some nice carbon-fibre bits. I bought her on 25/05/13 with 18276 miles from Cooperb motorcycles, Northants, who gave her a full service including valve check and adjustment and an HPI check (still have the paperwork). She has been fitted with RME rearsets (with vertical rear master cylinder mount), Fabbri tinted double-bubble screen, a full Renegade 2into2 exhaust system with high level cans and removable MOT baffles (sounds like an angry bull in a thunderstorm), Renegade open airbox conversion and forzaapriliaracing custom eprom chip to suit. I have cleaned and re-oiled the foam air filter and repacked the endcans. She also has E-marked LED rear lights which integrate the tail, brake and indicator lights. Looks smart. At 18972 miles I fitted new sprockets (16 tooth front, 43 tooth rear) and a DID X-ring chain. At 19416 miles I fitted new throttle cables, brake pads and wheel bearings all round. Last week at 21151 miles I stripped, cleaned and greased the shock linkages and fitted new bearings, bushes and seals to the dogbone. I removed the alarm/immobiliser as it had become faulty. The large brown block connector for the regulator/rectifier on these bikes has a habit of overheating so I have removed that and properly soldered and heatshrink wrapped the three wires which is a big improvement. I have also fitted a brand new gel battery and replaced the 50 amp starter solenoid with a 150 amp unit. There is a good bit of paperwork with her including V5C, service book stamped up to 18276 miles, all the previous MOTs, some receipts for bits and bobs, original bill of sale and owner's handbook. Well, I think I've covered everything. She has been a great, reliable bike for me and never fails to put a huge grin on my face. Goes like stink and sounds awesome! These bikes are becoming collectable and will surely gain in value. I don't really want to sell her but I'd like to get the kids into trials bikes so she has to go. Viewing and test rides are welcome. Obviously you'd need licence and insurance and the full asking price in my hand. You bend it you buy it. If you would like it delivered I'll do it for 10p/mile both ways (eg 200 miles = £40). PH404PJ if you want to check the distance. Thanks for looking.

product.description: For Sale are 2 Moto Guzzi Zigolo's. Both have V5C Registration Documents and both are registered in my name. I have owned both of these bikes for many many years. Both have in section 2 on the V5C's "NONE" for The previous registered keepers. There is a 99% complete 110cc and the remains of a 98cc. The 110cc was registered in 1957 and the 98cc was registered in 1960. INFO ABOUT THE 110cc The 110cc in quite nice condition with V5c. It has been stored away partly dismantled in my loft for approx 25 years. I dismantled it so that I could get it into the loft. It was running ok when I took it apart. I put it back together last year as my son said he would like it but has now decided he wants a car. I had it running after putting it back together last year, but since then it has not been started. It needs some 2 stroke petrol and a new exhaust gasket. Over the years I have bought many new parts for it with some that are quite rare and genuine zigolo parts :- new horn, new rear light unit, new headlamp rim and reflector, new horn/ dip switch with wiring loom, new aluminium engine covers, new exhaust pipe and silencer, new rear chain. The seat has been recovered and never used. Most of these parts came from Stanley Woods. ex TT winner and Moto Guzzi Dealer in Ireland in the 1980s / 90s. The frame and engine numbers do not match but the original engine with matching numbers to the frame comes with it. This engine is dismantled, so needs rebuilding. The paintwork and chrome are OK but not perfect. In the picture the bike is stood on a concrete block. The centre stand is with it but needs a new return spring fitting. It needs headlight and tail light bulbs. It needs an exhaust gasket. It needs a speedo drive/cable. There are 4 new Moto Guzzi transfers. 2 new Zigolo 110cc transfers. 110cc engine gasket set (partly used) INFO ABOUT THE 98cc Parts that I have that have also been stored away in my loft :- Frame with V5C Swinging arm. Top and bottom forks yolks. Headlamp shell. Rear chain guard. Rear light fitment (incomplete). 2 new rear sprockets. 3 engine sprockets. Engine (dismantled). Carburettor. Rear brake rod and bits. Extra spare barrel and piston. Horn / dip switch. Assorted nuts and bolts. 98cc Service Manual.

product.description: A opportunity to purchase a bike to show and/or as an investment. This 1976 Honda ST70 Monkeybike has had a complete strip down, nut and bolt restoration (using genuine Honda spares) with no expense spared. These lovely little bikes are becoming very hard to find and although most genuine Honda spares are still available the cost of renovating these bikes (excluding labour) can prove to be extremely expensive. They are, however ever increasing in rarity and value. This unique bike was displayed recently on Morton's concours stand at the Stafford Motorcycle Mechanics Bike show over the weekend of 17th & 18th October and attracted a lot of interest (regrettably "for sale" signs are not allowed on the concourse display). One of the advantages of these bikes is that they can be transported in most large cars/estates. Drive sprocket. Cooling: New radiators, hoses, clips, louvers. Impeller seals and bearings. Pressure tested. Electrics: New kill switch fitted, all parts of the CDI tested and sealed against moisture. Chassis: weld crack tested, re painted using KX colour code, new steering head bearings and seals, larger foot pegs fitted. gripper seat cover, all plastics throughout. decals, handle bars and grips. product.productName: Classic Triumph Daytona 1000. A rare bike, recently rebuilt.
product.description: Here we have my rebuilt 1991 (but first registered 1993) Triumph Daytona 1000 in what they've called Assam Black. This bike is in really good condition, having been rebuilt by me over the winter months. I bought it as a bit of a wreck last September and have spent the last five months bringing it back to life and putting it on the road. It was in a real state and some real 'nuts and bolts' work has been done, like replacing rotted subframes and, of course, horrible jobs like greasing the swingarm bearings have all been done. I didn't rebuild the engine (I thought I'd leave that until this coming winter) and it's still not perfect, but it's really good, and it's certainly a lot of fun to ride, especially since I rebuilt the front forks and made sure that the front suspension is all ok. To give an idea of what's been done and what's been spent, I've copied below the details from the file I kept. Some of this is for tools which I needed, but most of it is stuff which is now on the machine: 23-Oct-15 Cost of bike 650 23-Oct-15 Man with van 80 04-Nov-15 De greaser 6.21 06-Nov-15 m/c screws 2.95 10-Nov-15 throttle cable 12.85 10-Nov-15 Radiator guard 13.74 13-Nov-15 Carb spray 9.4 13-Nov-15 Gearchange rubber/Pushrod assembly etc 34.4 15-Nov-15 Chain breaker 11.58 18-Nov-15 Solenoid Bracket 13.98 18-Nov-15 Battery box bracket 13.98 18-Nov-15 Centre stand plates & springs 9 22-Nov-15 Carb rebuild stuff 89.88 29-Nov-15 36mm socket 7.49 29-Nov-15 30" breaker bar 11.99 30-Nov-15 K & N filter/Chain/Sprockets 142.53 06-Dec-15 Swing arm pivot bolt 6.75 07-Dec-15 Degreaser 4.85 07-Dec-15 Seals/Grease nipple covers 18.52 08-Dec-15 Red grease 8.9 08-Dec-15 Rear suspension linkage 22.99 13-Dec-15 Engine case bolts 15 15-Dec-15 Centre stand 52.98 16-Dec-15 Bolts/Locknuts/retaining rings 24.4 17-Dec-15 Exhaust hangers 16.95 19-Dec-15 Rear brake m/c 28.8 19-Dec-15 SBS Rear brake pads 18.99 19-Dec-15 Chain riveter 7.99 19-Dec-15 rear brake seal kit 20.5 27-Dec-15 Oil feed pipes OEM 50 30-Dec-15 Cam seal kit & rear M/c 33.94 03-Jan-16 Oil coller bracket 25 10-Jan-16 Battery 87.93 10-Jan-16 Qximiser leads 8.99 16-Jan-16 Oil Cooler 43.94 17-Jan-16 Cambi spanners 4.75 22-Jan-16 battery strap/Grommets/Gaskets 22.77 22-Jan-16 Nosecone subframe 36.98 26-Jan-16 Black paint 6.97 26-Jan-16 Acrylic clear coat 7.49 28-Jan-16 Caliper pinch bolts 6.99 30-Jan-16 Fork caps & seals 96.39 31-Jan-16 Fork oil 9.88 04-Feb-16 Front brake seal kit 48 08-Feb-16 Dremel brushes 10.75 10-Feb-16 Rear hugger 45 10-Feb-16 Front calipers 78.99 11-Feb-16 SBS Front brake pads 34.99 20-Feb-16 Indicator Relay 11.99 23-Feb-16 MOT and Chain Rivet (Ian Murray) 42.85 24-Feb-16 Decals/Mirror spacer 25.74 26-Feb-16 Tubular top rack 79.99 27-Feb-16 Sea foam 15.95 28-Feb-16 Cockpit infil panels 9.99 28-Feb-16 LHS Fairing infil 9.99 06-Mar-16 Union flag decals 3.98 06-Mar-16 Footpeg rubbers & bolts 14.9 TOTAL 2232.73 I'm speculatively starting to hunt around for a tourer, because I'm hatching plans for the summer. In the past, I've owned Honda Pans and BMW RTs so I know those bikes pretty well. So, if you've got something of similar value and you think you might be looking to change for something a bit different, please get in touch. But I'm not in a big rush to change and please don't ask me to swap for anything worth less than what I've spent. I could actually go touring on this quite happily I think, but I thought I'd test the water and see what's about. If I do end up keeping it, I'd be looking to replace the tupperware and strip and rebuild the engine this coming winter. Triumph only made a few hundred of these and there can't be many left on the road now, especially in this sort of condition. I reckon it'll only go up in value. I've got the V5 and it's MOTd until February 2017. It's got dealer service stamps to 33,000 miles, and it's currently got 67000 on the clock. I should say that, since I took the photos just after its MOT, I have put new decals on the lower fairing so those are good again now. there are still some marks on the fairings themselves, but they're not too horrendous! Am looking for a tourer (Honda Pan, BMW RT) or an Adventure bike (V-strom etc) Thanks for looking.

product.description: Triumph Thunderbird 900-1995 Carb Model- Totally Overhauled -New Sprag Clutch. Triumph's Thunderbird 900 Triple - A 1995 Appreciating Classic Benefitting from recently completed 'No Budget' Comprehensive Refurbishment. Restored with no restraint to Expenditure on Parts & Labour. Complimented by many Enhancing Improvements using mainly Triumph Quality Parts. It has been Thoughtfully & Thoroughly Upgraded whilst retaining it's Original Akron Polished Alloy Wheel Rims & S/S Spokes. Alloy Engine Casings & Rocker Cover. Mikuni Carburettors. Key Locking Saddle. Plus Genuine Triumph Extras :-Center Stand.- Triumph Sissy Bar & Rack.- King & Queen seat. Bought having just past its M.O.T. with No Advisories at 32,918. Miles. The sole intention being to put it back to as near new as your likely to find. That is now done. & as planned it's up for sale to someone looking for a really smart well sorted genuine 1995 Thunderbird. 365 pictures on C.D. Show the amount of meticulous work undertaken to bring it back to it's present condition. This Thunderbird was Completely Stripped Down. All parts individually cleaned - refurbished - upgraded or replaced. Engine removed & stripped down for a check over & installation of a 'New Sprag Clutch'. Crank Case re-sprayed, all New Gaskets & Seals. New S/S Manifold Studs & Nuts, New spark plugs. Casings polished. New Ignition pick up & Three Brand New Coils. New K&N oil filter, Fresh Semi/ Synthetic Engine Oil, Carburettors cleaned inside & out I also had a Stage 1-3 Jet Kit made up specifically for this bike by 'Sigma U.S.A'. carbs then re-assembled with all New Seals, float levels re-set, carbs balanced. new K&N air filter. & New Throttle Cable. --- Read 'Sigma's statement :- This is not just some jets in a box, where you get to guess at what you need, and pull your carburettor 10 times trying to figure it out, it is a comprehensive Custom Engineered 6Sigma Jet Kit, addressing all throttle positions, throttle response. Each kit is Custom Engineered by 6Sigma to your bike and its modifications. Replacing just the jets does not address 1/4-3/4 throttle, or throttle response, only full throttle. This Kit is for all throttle positions, and throttle response. This is a tuner kit, to get everything out of your bike, that it can give. The removed clutch slave cleaned sprayed & Re-built it with New piston & seals. Drive sprocket checked out good as did rear sprocket. Chain Cleaned & all good. Swing Arm & Suspension Spring cleaned & checked out Pivots Greased. Rear mudguard cleaned underside & re-sprayed. A New Number Plate is on re-furbed brackets. Many Old Nuts Bolts Washers etc replaced with Stainless Steel as available & appropriate. Both Brake Callipers stripped cleaned & re-built with new seals new S/S Pad Retainer Pin + Plug plus Bleed Nipples & New Nissan Disc Pads. New Rear Disc - Both discs have New S/S disc bolts, S/S Braided lines to Both Brakes & Clutch. New Adjustable Brake & Clutch Levers. All Three Master Cylinders Stripped Cleaned & Rebuilt with New Full Service kits & S/S cap screws. Both front Masters re-sprayed black after the fitting of new clear glass to inspection ports. Front forks stripped for installation of Taper Roller Bearings to Top & Bottom Yokes which were cleaned & re-sprayed, fork legs drained & flushed, Progressive Springs Installed with fresh Shell Advanced Fork Oil. Bottom Legs cleaned & re- sprayed with Clear Lacquer. Alloy Wheel rims polished. Both Wheels have Stainlees Steel Spokes, & new dust seals. New Matching 'AVON' Road Rider Tyres with New Heavy Duty Inner Tubes. Front mudguard-brace cleared of debris + w/proofed & sealed. refit with S/S Bolts plus a new Fender Extender. Front rebuilt Calliper has new S/S fixing bolts. Instrument units stripped + cleaned. Chrome Headlight re-sprayed Inside. All harness connections opened cleaned & treated with ACF-50 as were the battery box fuse box ECU etc. Starter Motor removed checked re sprayed connections cleaned & new case seal, Alternator removed re sprayed & installed with New Cush Rubber kit. Fuel tank valve serviced & filter cleaned. Tank is clean & sound. Radiator cleaned internally & out / repainted as necessary. Fan / Thermostat / water pump / all removed cleaned & checked. System checked sound with fresh Correct Anti Freeze / Distilled water mix. Both Side Stand & Center Stand are in excellent order. Despite being in good condition I had the Triumph King & Queen saddle Professionally upgraded with New Quality Cloth buttons & red piping/stitching, only back panel reused (it has Triumph Imprinted). The Battery is recent & has an Optimate Connector. The retained Original Exhaust System's S/S headers were cleaned of old chrome & are now VHT Sprayed Matt Black, & fitted with New Short Megaphone Silencers, these are easily altered by simple baffle & or wadding removal, via end cap. Originals also come with the bike, as do the last seven years M.O.T's that show mileage continuation & no advisories. Now on 03-11-15 completed, it has a fresh M.O.T. product.productName: 2007 Honda CBR 125R for sale, only 8000 on clock!
product.description: Selling on behalf of my brother, we have for sale a 2007 CBR 125R with only 8000 on the clock. There have been 6 registered keepers of the bike, but two of these are me! I have owned the bike (twice) since 2014. As expected with a 125 learner bike and a bike of this age, it does have some cosmetic damage which we have tried to show in the pictures. It has some chips and a dent to the tank, it had some cracks to the fairings, a scuff on the front light and the indicators are secured with tape. It also has a slightly sticky gear selector. I have loved this bike in the time I have owned it, hence owning it twice! It was well looked after and serviced at the back end of 2014 with only approx. 1000 miles added to it since. In the time I have owned the bike, the chain, sprocket and spindle have been replaced, the chain regularly lubed and it has been regularly cleaned. It has both keys and alarm fobs, I will also throw the Oxford lock. I used this bike to pass my test and now ride a 650, hence the sale as it is no longer required. It is a great learner bike, fun to ride and one of the best looking 125's around (in my opinion). These bikes do hold their value, but considering the cosmetic damage this has reflected in the price. I am looking in the region of £1200, but will consider reasonable offers. It is currently on SORN, with the MOT expiring on the 16th May 2016, I see no reason why this would not fly through its next MOT. Due to working shifts, my sister will deal with any initial queries but I am happy for anyone to come and take a look at the bike at mutual convenience. The bike is in Stevenage, Hertfordshire. More photos available on request.

product.productName: 2010 YAMAHA YZF R1 10 BLUE road legal track race bike
product.description: Here we have my beloved 2010 yamaha yzf r1 which i have owned since late 2012 and has done a genuine 5207 miles from new. 1 previous owner. I have all three keys including the red master key Always run on the higher octane rated 'super unleaded' (usually shell v power nitro or tesco momentum 99 which it was mapped on) Always warmed up properly before use Full service history (just had oil and filter changed again) (I have always used hi flo filtro oil filters and castrol power 1 racing 10w40 oil) I have converted it into a road legal track bike (daytime mot) It has the following upgrades: Blue hel stainless steel brake lines front and rear DOT 5.1 brake fluid Recent EBC GPFAX front pads fitted Bridgestone r10 tyres (part worn) Brembo rcs 19 brake master cylinder brembo clutch lever and perch (matches rcs 19) TRW adjustable rear sets (rear brake lever bobbin vibrated lose and was lost so i have replaced with a bolt and nyloc nut and sleeved a bit of rubber hose over the top) Renthal Gen 1 clip on handlebars Renthal kevlar road race grips R&G crash bobbins (front fork/axle and two lots of side aero style crash protectors) (upper and lower) Rear paddock stand/ crash bobbins Tank grip keyless aluminium fuel cap Active quick action throttle kit Renthal sprockets (hard anodised rear) (-1 front / +1 rear) (520) Tsubaki pro racing chain (520) Tail tidy number plate bracket Pro fiber fibre glass race fairings, sbk seat unit with stick on foam pad and front mudgaurd Pro fiber carbon fibre race air intakes (flow better for a few extra hp) Pro fiber carbon fibre instrument cluster / front fairing support Pro fiber carbon fibre engine casing protectors (3 pieces) (kevlar reinforced) Clear double bubble race screen from Dennis Trollope Racing Samco sport blue silicon coolant hose kit akrapovic exhaust system (full titanium with no DB killers (99db at 5500 rpm static) (i think its an evolution line kit system) (bought from Ryan Fairweather who had a bike built for him by shaun Muir when he was running swan yamaha team so maybe a bit special as it looks like a different/bigger link pipe....) Ohlins SD 024 steering damper Ohlins TTX mkII YA 931 shock absorber Ohlins FGRT 206 front forks K&N race air filter secondary air injection system has been removed and blanked Cordona Ecu based quick shifter (quickshifter map done by John Ewles also) (works much better and smoother than standalone hm plus i was using previously) Ecu has been flash tuned by John Ewles at track electronics (174.22bhp at the rear wheel and 76.71Ft/lb of torque with dyno print out) Data-link ECU flashing kit will also come with the bike ( I have left it installed on the bike so that changes can be made quickly and easily if need be. There is probably something i have missed on the list...... I have dropped the bike at Snetterton at low speed (lowside at Murrays) which is what caused a bit of wear on one crash bung and cracked the rear seat unit and put a small dent in one of the silencer outer sleeves. All cosmetic and does not affect the performance or ride of the bike) Mot expired october 6th 2014 but i will get a new Mot on the bike when it sells £6499 Any questions then please feel free to message me

product.description: Hi all right then where do I begin... I am going to do 2 versions of this ad. The short version :- Very Reliable Classic 1987 Kawasaki KLR 250 -D4 (28BHP) (Liquid Cooled) With Valuable Numberplate. Low Milage for year. Taxed and Tested, Good Overall Condition. Any questions please ask. And for those who want to The Long Long Version :- Up for Sale A Classic / Vintage 1987 Kawasaki KLR250 (D4) Quite rare in this colour. Engine Sweet, Gearbox Smooth, No Oil or Water Leaks. This would make for a great learner bike as the power output falls within the new A2 restriction bracket, So Learner Legal. A Superb Old School Green laner 4 Stoke Work horse. It will plod along all day every day. I have done about 5 Thousand miles on this bike and it's never let me down not once. I would have no hesitation taking this bike anywhere, For any Distance. I Have all the paperwork for this bike in my name. (Owned it for Quite a few years) Cheap Tax, Cheap Insurance (Classic so only £62 for the year for me) Cheap Running Cost too with Kawasaki Reliability. Starts 2nd kick from Stone cold everytime and it runs great all day. 1st Kick Warm everytime. There's a few Spare parts A UFO Mudguard A Full size Numberplate, Front disc cover etc ... Over the years I have spent time, money and effort Keeping it in good order. It now benefits from :- Led Back light Tail Tidy (Original Included In Sale) Gold Chain + Sprockets replaced last year Geared up 1 tooth for Easier cruising (Still no slouch though it go's well for a 250) Maybe because it's a double overhead cam. Recent front tyre. Rear Brake Shoes Replaced 3 weeks ago. Recent Front Brake Pads. HandGuards. Braided Front Brake Hose (Much better Braking) Original Included. Led Indicators. New Piston fitted about 1800 miles ago (Did an Engine overhaul) Skull Hand Mirrors. Rack + TopBox (2 Keys) Small Numberplate (Full size Plate Included) VIP You need to be about 5 foot 10 to be able to reach the floor as this is A Very Tall Bike. Seat Height 900mm (Lowest Point) Links can be bought to lower the height, Misplaced the Originals. Bar height 1130mm Standard wear and tear for a bike of 28 years old. Very Low Mileage for a bike 28 Years Old This bike has been well looked after ( I do an oil and Filter change every 500 miles). Valves clearances set 200 miles ago. This has got to be by far the best bike I have ever had the pleasure of owning and riding for the last few Years. But Sadly It has to go. I Need to buy something lighter with Electric start. (Health Problems forces the sale) I had a Numberplate valuation done last year by Capital Reg, They valued the plate at £1400 (Not the Bike Just the Plate) Great Bike, Gears change smooth, Easy to start warm or cold, Get on it and ride all day. Sweet Smooth Clean Dry Engine. There is a website called "How many left. c o m" That says In the 3rd Quater of 2015 there was Only 8 left On the road and 22 Sorn see link:- So this means buying this bike would also be a good investment as it will only increase more in value over time, At the end of the day there's only 30 left. (Yet parts still easy to get hold of) Collection From TS134 or will consider delivery if I get my train fair home. (Within Reaon of course) Wiewing welcomed as are test rides with the cash in my hand (If you bend it you bought it though). I can also take anyone out for a run as a pillion if needed. Please don't buy this bike and Expect a new looking bike this KLR is the thick end of 30 Years old. Photos show a true likeness and were taken today. It is what it is I have not tried to polish it and make it into something it's not. Issues worth mentioning:- This is rather odd but the Back brake seems to be biting and letting go A bit once it's been stood a while, However if I drive round the block with the brake slightly on this go's away. Just being honest. (May jusy need bedding in) or Perhaps A honing tool would clean the surface of the inside of the drum up. This has only happened since fitting the new Brake shoes the other week. Fuel tap is On or On (Not Leaking Though) Needs A new Battery.(Old one had it, Go's flat overnight) It really is a Clean Example of a bike for this age in Quite Original Un-Molested Condition. Mileage will increase slightly as it's still being used. I think that's it, I have been totally honest in the listing but on the off chance you do have a question please ask. product.description: Before we start and sorry to some real buyers about this rant, but I am losing the will to live with some people out there. The is just 1 like this one for sale on eBay and they are asking £2300 for it and it's clocking a very high 60000 miles on the clock to the difference in my one at 24000 miles on the clock and the same owner for the past 28 years, that spent no end of money in upkeep maintenance to keep it looking and running A1. The is only one thing that is missing on the bike, what I would call aluminum foil decals, that did not deal too well with a bike that is over 3 decades old, apart from that it's 100% original and priced £500 cheaper than the very high mileage one for sale on ebay. That I am more than sure that the rest of the bike don't come close to the same condition, including the engine and all wearable parts, frame and so forth. If not sold, I will just keep it being messed around way too much by time wasters for no reason, yes I will have the bike, I will be at yours on Sat, I will be at yours on Tuesday, I will take it for sure on Friday don't sell it, and list is endless, to then not turn up and mess up my day and plans for no reason. All the email and questions/interest I am getting for my Honda is getting a bit ridiculous now, just come down and take a look at the bike and see me in person, if it's one of these great classic Honda's you are looking for, to collect or ride you will not in anyway be disappointed with this one for sure, it's a proper 33 year old genuine bike that has been well taken care of and has had no end of upkeep work done by the same owner for that past 28 years. All that out of the way finally, this is my ad for my mint Honda :))))))) To all the classic Honda enthusiasts, I have for sale a beautiful machine, that I agreed to take px for my like brand new Yamaha that I had to sell due to personal reasons. I decided to do the deal has I have not seen one of these great machines in this condition since I was around 8 years old, and that is going back a bit. Classic 82 reg Honda Nighthawk 650 cc, low mileage, same caring owner for the past 28 years. I will start by saying that the photos were taken on a miserable day, and they really don't do the bike justice, this bike is in fantastic condition for 33 year old and very well cared for and maintained. I would go so far as to say, one of the best remaining examples of a UK non import Honda Nighthawk 650 cc left in the country, not only a rare, but very rare in this great condition. Where to start with this bike that looks great. 1) Chrome all around in great condition 2) Frame in great condition 3) Fairings in great condition 4) New spark plugs and lines 5) Battery in good working order and fairly new. 6) New tyres back and front 7) Engine starts and runs spot on every time. 8) All electrics in fully working order 9) Brakes work as they should 10) Forks are in great condition and new seals not long back. I may have missed some good points out, but you just need to ask if you would like to know more. No bad points that I can see with my fine eye for detail, comes with manual, logbook and both keys. I have seen these bikes on eBay sell for £1200 to £1400 in very poor condition, very high milage and has spare and repair. This one is in fantastic condition, low milage and well worth my asking price. £1800 ono.................Sensible offers and possible px welcome. Please no time wasters, day dreamers and stupid offers, this is a collectible spec 33 year old Honda and will just go up and up in value. product.description: Suzuki V-Strom 650 DL 2008 I always wanted a Suzuki V-strom 650 DL I had ideas of touring Europe with my Wife on the back of it seeing far flung sights riding up and down twisty mountain passes over the Pyranees so I saved and saved which is no easy task when raising a family of four kids but I stayed patient and one day I had enough pennies in the bank to be able to buy one. I spent a few weeks trawling the internet along with papers and magazines then one turned up that I really liked three hours north of where I live but no worries off I went all was as it seemed and I bought it enjoying the ride home down the A1. That's about as happy as I have been with it because as it has turned out over the last six months I have realised I really don't like the sitting upright positioning of this type of bike, the V twin is not to my tastes and even though the bike is spot on and looks great I have decided to head back to my sports tourer roots with a nice carb set up. So what's on offer? It's a Suzuki V-Strom 650 DL 2008 registration with approx 28000 (used daily so will go up) miles on the clock and an MOT until June 2016. It has a Givi top box and side panniers plus a solid tank bag a sat nav holder and Oxford heated grips that work a treat. I have fitted a new pair of Pilot 4 Dual compound tyres replacing the horrible ones in the picture at a cost of £300 and I have removed the cheap spot lights that were fitted by the last owner. There's a beak on it and headlight protector. Once it is sold I will buy myself a nice sports tourer or maybe even a custom type ride who knows what will come along. So if you want a V-strom this one is in great condition with new tyres not long serviced and ready to go. It is Sold As Seen with no warranty implied or given (I hate selling motors and do it very rarely so please make sure you are happy with it before you buy) but I am happy for you to have it checked out by the AA RAC ect before purchase. Test rides are welcome but you must show me proof of insurance and give me the full asking price in cash to hold before you take it out...you break it you have bought it! The price is set below no haggling no offers because that is less than it stands me at! If I don't sell it I will keep riding it until next spring and re advertise then so I am in no rush at all :) I may be interested in a part exchange or a swap for a Land Rover Defender I am based in the NG5 area of Nottingham. Thanks for reading.
